<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-798-446  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 798 446.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  August 27 1990 n383 p20(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New Unix spec may prod developers. (standard from ATandamp;T, Intel andThe Santa Cruz Operation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Clancy, Heather.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The consortium of Intel Corp, The Santa Cruz Operation and AT andT Unix System Laboratories Inc have agreed on a new specificationcalled the Intel Binary Compatibility Specification Edition 2(iBCS 2) for unix software development.andP;  The specification willlet software developers like Lotus Development Corp create oneshrink-wrapped version of a program that will run on Intel 80386and 80486-based Unix operating systems.andP;  The second edition of thestandard removes some compatibility problems that were found inthe first installment, and the improvements will be included inupgrades of the operating systems within the next six months.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Santa Cruz Operation Inc. (standards)Intel Corp. (standards)American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (standards).andO;Ticker:    T; INTC.andO;Topic:     UNIXStandardizationOperating SystemsUNIX-Like Operating SystemsConsortiaCompatibilitySoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>